org.actus.events

Class EventSequence

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.actus.events.EventSequence

  • public final class EventSequence
extends Object
    Component that represents the sequence of ContractEvents at a certain time

    Various ContractEvents happen during the lifetime of a . Some events may happen at exactly the same point in time. In this case, the EventSequence defines the sequence in which the events are being processed. Therefore, events are ordered according to their time and processing order (i.e. event sequence) represented by a time offset in the EventSeries.

    This component contains all definitions of event sequence time offsets which are being used when ordering events in the EventSeries.
